# alias tag

The **alias** tag provides a way to create references to specific URLs. Each of these can reference a parent **alias** in order to construct cascading paths, similar to a poor man's C macro.

```html

    <alias name="CONTENT_ROOT" url="/public/app/html"  />
    <alias name="PAGES"Â url="pages" path="CONTENT_ROOT"  />
    <alias name="CHART_PAGE" url="charts.html" path="PAGES" />
<alias name="CREDITS_PAGE" url="credits.html" path="PAGES" />

```

Using **alias** , you can refactor the directory structure of an existing application, changing files and locations without modifying the underlying code.




   


